{"parentUuid": null, "isSidechain": true, "promptId": "6c3a0b22-aa71-4abe-86b8-7ed7f2e35c75", "agentId": "aadea7500d3465cd2", "type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": "Adversarially verify this finding about a design doc (the doc is at /tmp/claude-1000/-home-jleechan-projects-worktree-runner/8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b/scratchpad/gistfile1.txt; the repo is /home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner; you may use WebSearch/WebFetch and read files). Try to REFUTE it. Finding from the \"facts\" reviewer, severity critical:\nTITLE: gha-outrunner exists but is an extremely obscure single-maintainer project (3 stars, 0 forks)\nDETAIL: VERIFIED: The project exists at https://github.com/NetwindHQ/gha-outrunner ('Ephemeral VM and container runners for GitHub Actions \u2014 no Kubernetes required'). It genuinely matches the design's assumptions: written in Go, MIT licensed, supports exactly the three backends the design names (Docker, libvirt/KVM qcow2, Tart on Apple Silicon), and registers via GitHub's scaleset API as an autoscaling runner group without Kubernetes. It is actively maintained \u2014 latest release v1.2.0 on April 20, 2026, 5 total releases, built by Pawel Subocz at Netwind. HOWEVER, at fetch time it has 3 stars, 0 forks, 17 open issues, and a single author. The entire gha-isolated design wraps this project as its execution engine, so the design inherits a severe bus-factor and abandonment risk from a project with essentially no community. The author did NOT confuse it with actions-runner-controller, rust-lang/gha-runner, omsf/gha-runner, or runs-on.com \u2014 those are distinct projects. Evidence: https://github.com/NetwindHQ/gha-outrunner\nRECOMMENDATION: Acknowledge the dependency risk explicitly in the design. Options: (a) vendor/fork gha-outrunner since it is MIT, (b) build on GitHub's official standalone scale set client (https://github.com/actions/scaleset, public preview Feb 2026) as the durable API layer with gha-outrunner as reference code, or (c) contribute the wrapper features upstream to gha-outrunner instead of wrapping it.\nIs the finding factually correct and does the recommendation make sense? If the factual basis is wrong or the severity is inflated, refute it. Default to refuted=true only if you have concrete contrary evidence or the claim is unsupported after checking."}, "uuid": "4fda88e0-65a6-49d6-b83e-1c7fd6827d85", "timestamp": "2026-07-03T22:00:27.957Z", "userType": "external", "entrypoint": "cli", "cwd": "/home/jleechan/projects/worktree_runner", "sessionId": "8ca589dd-8422-44b1-a543-52bd7b71f14b", "version": "2.1.198", "gitBranch": "fix/linux-runner-pre-job-hook", "slug": "velvet-wishing-cake"}
